      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 0,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      661.65,
      543.04,
      674.93
    ],
    "text": "This appeal emanates from the Order made by the learned High Court Judge of Embilipitiya",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 0,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      682.4,
      543.06,
      695.69
    ],
    "text": "dismissing the revision application of the Respondent-Petitioner-Appellant made against the Order",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 0,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      703.04,
      360.31,
      716.33
    ],
    "text": "of the learned Magistrate of Embilipitiya dated 02.07.2015.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 0,
    "bbox": [
      72.74,
      225.13,
      201.17,
      349.32
    ],
    "text": "Court of Appeal Case No: CA (PHC) 169/2017 High Court Embilipitiya Case: HCRA 11/15 Magistrates Court Embilipitiya Case No: 12948/15",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman",
      "Times New Roman,Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      72.23,
      543.02,
      85.51
    ],
    "text": "It appears that the Provincial High Court of Embilipitiya by Order dated 31.08.2017 dismissed the",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      92.89,
      542.89,
      106.17
    ],
    "text": "application of the Respondent-Petitioner-Appellant for want of jurisdiction on the basis that the",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      113.65,
      480.1,
      126.93
    ],
    "text": "Provincial High Court has no jurisdiction to review matters pertaining to state lands.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      134.29,
      543.04,
      163.53
    ],
    "text": "The Respondent has relied upon the Supreme Court Judgment in the case of The Superintendent,",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman",
      "Times New Roman,BoldItalic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      170.89,
      543.05,
      184.17
    ],
    "text": "Stafford Estate and Others Vs. Solaimuthu Rasu [(2013) 1 S.L.R 25], which held that the",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman",
      "Times New Roman,BoldItalic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      191.65,
      542.9,
      204.93
    ],
    "text": "Provincial High Court has no jurisdiction over matters related to state lands, as powers relating to",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      211.26,
      543.1,
      225.57
    ],
    "text": "state lands have not been devolved on the Provincial Councils by the 13th Amendment to the",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      8.039999961853027,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      233.05,
      542.64,
      246.33
    ],
    "text": "Constitution. It is seen that the aforesaid case was a matter related to the writ jurisdiction of the",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      253.69,
      332.35,
      266.97
    ],
    "text": "Provincial High Court over a decision on a state land.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      274.36,
      543.02,
      301.56
    ],
    "text": "It is seen that, the learned Judge of the High Court of Embilipitiya had obviously followed the",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      308.92,
      543.1,
      322.2
    ],
    "text": "Judgment of The Superitendent, Stafford Estate & Two others Vs. Solaimuthu Rasu [supra],",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman",
      "Times New Roman,BoldItalic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      329.68,
      543.02,
      342.96
    ],
    "text": "which is a writ application. However, as many Judgments and authorities have held, the High Court",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      350.32,
      542.94,
      363.6
    ],
    "text": "acting under Article 138 of the Constitution, has jurisdiction to try and hear revision applications",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      371.08,
      180.38,
      384.36
    ],
    "text": "relating to state lands.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      391.6,
      543.09,
      418.8
    ],
    "text": "It is relevant to note that the ratio decidendi of the Judgment in Solaimuthu Rasus case, which",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman",
      "Times New Roman,BoldItalic",
      "Times New Roman,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      426.16,
      542.92,
      439.44
    ],
    "text": "held that the Provincial High Court had no jurisdiction to issue writs under Article 154P (4) of the",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      446.94,
      262.73,
      460.22
    ],
    "text": "Constitution pertaining to State lands.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      467.46,
      542.69,
      494.66
    ],
    "text": "In order for the Provincial High Courts to exercise writ jurisdiction, the issue should be one that",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      502.14,
      543.0,
      515.42
    ],
    "text": "falls within the purview of the Provincial Council list. Since the subject-State lands does not fall",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      522.78,
      542.84,
      536.06
    ],
    "text": "within the purview of the Provincial Council list, Provincial High Court is not empowered to issue",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      543.54,
      532.42,
      556.82
    ],
    "text": "writs under Article 154P (4) of the Constitution in respect of matters pertaining to State lands.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      564.06,
      542.94,
      591.26
    ],
    "text": "According to Article 154P (3) (b) of the Constitution, which stipulates that, Every such High",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      598.74,
      542.83,
      612.02
    ],
    "text": "Court shall notwithstanding anything in Article 138 and subject to any Law, exercise appellate and",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      619.41,
      542.87,
      632.69
    ],
    "text": "revisionary jurisdiction in respect of convictions, sentences and orders entered or imposed by",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      640.17,
      377.71,
      653.45
    ],
    "text": "Magistrates Courts and Primary Courts within the province.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      660.69,
      542.68,
      687.89
    ],
    "text": "It is noteworthy that revisionary jurisdiction in terms of Article 154P (3) (b) of the Constitution,",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      695.36,
      548.26,
      708.65
    ],
    "text": "has not excluded the power to exercise appellate or revisionary jurisdiction regarding State lands.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      72.11,
      542.97,
      99.33
    ],
    "text": "It is observable that the Respondent-Petitioner-Appellant had invoked the revisionary jurisdiction",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      106.69,
      542.99,
      119.97
    ],
    "text": "of the Provincial High Court of Embilipitiya in terms of Article 154P (3) (b), and not under Article",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      127.45,
      218.69,
      140.73
    ],
    "text": "154P (4) of the Constitution.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      147.97,
      542.75,
      175.17
    ],
    "text": "Therefore, it appears that the learned High Court Judge has misconstrued the Articles of the",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      182.65,
      543.03,
      195.93
    ],
    "text": "Constitution and also relied on the Judgment of Solaimuthu Rasu expressing his view that any",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman",
      "Times New Roman,BoldItalic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      203.29,
      545.74,
      216.57
    ],
    "text": "matter relating to State lands could not be reviewed in any manner in the Provincial High Court.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      224.05,
      542.86,
      237.33
    ],
    "text": "As such, it is apparent that the Order made by the learned High Court Judge dismissing the revision",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      244.69,
      543.04,
      257.97
    ],
    "text": "application made by the Respondent-Petitioner-Appellant is made per incuriam. Therefore, the",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman",
      "Times New Roman,Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      265.48,
      492.46,
      278.76
    ],
    "text": "impugned Order dated 31.08.2017 made by the learned High Court Judge is set aside.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      286.0,
      539.9,
      313.2
    ],
    "text": "We take notice of the motion dated 07.06.2022 filed on behalf of the Applicant-Respondent-",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      320.68,
      542.91,
      333.96
    ],
    "text": "Respondent, stating its consent to have this matter sent back to the High Court of Embilipitiya for",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      341.32,
      543.08,
      354.6
    ],
    "text": "it to be considered on the merits. In view of the aforementioned reasons, we set aside the impugned",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      362.08,
      543.04,
      375.36
    ],
    "text": "Order of the learned High Court Judge of Embilipitiya dated 31.08.2017 and send this case back",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      382.72,
      530.74,
      396.0
    ],
    "text": "to the Provincial High Court of Embilipitiya to re-hear and determine this matter on its merits.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      403.36,
      543.03,
      430.56
    ],
    "text": "Thus, the appeal is allowed and Registrar is directed to send the case record back to the High Court",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      437.94,
      198.65,
      451.22
    ],
    "text": "of Embilipitiya forthwith.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      528.66,
      543.1,
      573.62
    ],
    "text": "JUDGE OF THE COURT OF APPEAL K.K.A.V. Swarnadhipathi, J.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman",
      "Times New Roman,Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      72.02,
      580.86,
      110.9,
      594.14
    ],
    "text": "I agree.",
    "fonts": [
      "Times New Roman"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
